reviews.review_text: Space->Dear Mr. Fantasy If you like the Mind Left Body Jam, you'll like this.

Ahhhh...Merriweather Saw the boys play here in 83,84,85..love,love,love this venue!Did I mention LOVE? My favorites are the two in 85.In my opinion special shows.The 1st set is solid,but the second set smokes.I remember being under the pavilion for the Scarlet>Fire {{WOW}} is all I can say.One of my favorite Dear Mr Fantasy ever!! and the double encore Satisfaction/Baby Blue
I left this show completely SATISFIED!!!!!!!One I will always remember
you had to be there... The quality of this recording is just fine and deserves the highest rating. remember the goonie birds..
okay Brutal 1st set until Let It Grow, then you have to stomach Keep Your Day Job.  2nd set is nice.  Merriweather is brutal unless you have a seat in the Pav.
Very Nice Uncle John's Band Of course, I'm partial to it....
Scarlet Been listening to this board for 23 years for that solo in Scarlet. Punctual, long and articulate. It's all about Scarlet here. And the Let it Grow ain't bad either.
Bobby on Walkin Love the lyrics in the first verse. You can tell everybody was feelin it the entire song, just kinda chugging along. Theeeeen they overplayed the shit out of it.

Scarlet Begonias  Been jamming to this scarlet for since 85, It's one of my fav's the jam is just spectalour! The Walking Blues is also worth a mention as it's like a punk rock version Lol. And the Let it Grow is raging good. They really rocked this show 85 style.
